ĢIn Memory of
Catherine De Sousa (1926-2018)
Who loved to sit in these gardens
"There are no strangers, only friends you have not met yet!"
(WB Yeats)"Ü
ŚThe Sorbus tree in the North side of the garden
was planted in memory of
Sir Terence Rattigan, CBE (1911-1977)
by David Suchet CBE
on 22nd May 2012"ø
śYoung Lovers seek perfection.
Old lovers learn the art of sewing shreds together.
And of seeing beauty in a multiplicity of patches
PRC to LMC - 1996"×
øSakura Cherry Tree Profect 2019 - 2022
Celebrating a new Era of Japan-UK Fiendship
Kawasaki Heavy Industries, Ltd.
Marubeni Corporation
MITSUI & CO LTD"ó
¤To the very dear memory of
Hannelore Nath "Anne"
who loved London and the changing of
the seasons in its beautiful parks and squares
Danzig 1932    London 2009"ż
Ī"fair Quiet, have I found thee here" (MARVELL)
"a garden is a lovesome thing" (BROWN)
Given by Bobbe & Myles Wilder
Temecula, California 1996 40th Anniversary"ź
